settings.name: starting_money
settings.description: Amount of gold when arriving at the farm. Set to -1 or unlimited for infinite money in this playthrough.

settings.name: resource_pack_multiplier
settings.description: How many items will be in the resource pack. A lower setting mean fewer resources in each pack. A higher setting means more resources in each pack. Easy (200) doubles the default quantity. This also include Friendship bonuses that replace the one from the Bulletin Board.

settings.name: bundle_randomization
settings.description: What items are needed for the community center bundles?

values.name: vanilla
values.description: You get the standard bundles from the game.

values.name: thematic
values.description: Every bundle will require random items within their original category.

values.name: shuffled
values.description: Every bundle will require random items without logic.

settings.name: bundle_price
settings.description: How many items are needed for the community center bundles?

settings.name: entrance_randomization
settings.description: Should area entrances be randomized?

values.name: pelican_town
values.description: Only buildings in the main town area are randomized with each other.

values.name: non_progression
values.description: Only buildings that are always available are randomized with each other.

settings.name: backpack_progression
settings.description: How is the backpack progression handled?

values.name: progressive
values.description: You will randomly find Progressive Backpack to upgrade.

values.name: early_progressive
values.description: You can expect you first Backpack before the second season, and the third before the fourth season.

settings.name: tool_progression
settings.description: How is the tool progression handled?

values.name: progressive
values.description: You will randomly find Progressive Tool to upgrade.

settings.name: skill_progression
settings.description: How is the skill progression handled?

values.name: progressive
values.description: Experience will be counted internally, and locations will be sent when you gain a virtual level. Your real levels will be scattered around the world.

settings.name: building_progression
settings.description: How is the building progression handled?

values.name: progressive
values.description: You will receive the buildings and will be able to build the first one of each building for free, once it is received. If you want more of the same building, it will cost the vanilla price. This option INCLUDES the shipping bin as a building you need to receive.

values.name: progressive_early_shipping_bin
values.description: You will receive the buildings and will be able to build the first one of each building for free, once it is received. If you want more of the same building, it will cost the vanilla price. This option INCLUDES the shipping bin as a building you need to receive, which can be expected before the end of the first season.

settings.name: elevator_progression
settings.description: How is The Mines' Elevator progression handled?

values.name: progressive
values.description: You will randomly find Progressive Mine Elevator to go deeper. Location are sent for reaching every level multiple of 5.

values.name: progressive_from_previous_floor
values.description: You will randomly find Progressive Mine Elevator to go deeper. Location are sent for taking the ladder or stair to every level multiple of 5, taking the elevator does not count.

settings.name: arcade_machine_locations
settings.description: How are the Arcade Machines handled?

values.name: victories
values.description: Each Arcade Machine will contain one check on victory.

values.name: victories_easy
values.description: The arcade machines are both made considerably easier to be more accessible for the average player.

values.name: full_shuffling
values.description: The arcade machines will contain multiple checks each, and different buffs that make the game easier are in the item pool. Junimo Kart has one check at the end of each level. Journey of the Prairie King has one check after each boss, plus one check for each vendor equipment.

settings.name: help_wanted_locations
settings.description: How many "Help Wanted" quests need to be completed as Archipelago Locations. Out of every 7 quests, 4 will be item deliveries, and then 1 of each for: Fishing, Gathering and Slaying Monsters. Choosing a multiple of 7 is recommended.

settings.name: fishsanity
settings.description: Locations for catching fish?

values.name: special
values.description: A curated selection of strong fish are locations that contain items.

settings.name: player_buff_number
settings.description: Number of buffs to the player of each type that exist as items in the pool. Buffs include movement speed (+25% multiplier, stacks additively) and daily luck bonus (0.025 flat value per buff).

settings.name: goal
settings.description: What's your goal with this play-through?

values.name: community_center
values.description: The world will be completed once you complete the Community Center.

values.name: grandpa_evaluation
values.description: The world will be completed once 4 candles are lit around Grandpa's Shrine.

values.name: bottom_of_the_mines
values.description: The world will be completed once you reach level 120 in the local mineshaft.

values.name: cryptic_note
values.description: The world will be completed once you complete the quest "Cryptic Note" where Mr Qi asks you to reach floor 100 in the Skull Cavern.

values.name: master_angler
values.description: The world will be completed once you have caught every fish in the game. Pairs well with Fishsanity.

settings.name: multiple_day_sleep_enabled
settings.description: Should you be able to sleep automatically multiple day straight?

settings.name: multiple_day_sleep_cost
settings.description: Determines how much gold per day that it costs to sleep through multiple days.

settings.name: experience_multiplier
settings.description: Determines how experience gains are multiplied.

settings.name: debris_multiplier
settings.description: How much debris spawns on the player's farm?

settings.name: quick_start
settings.description: Do you want the quick start package? You will get a few items to help early game automation, so you can use the multiple day sleep at its maximum.

settings.name: gifting
settings.description: Do you want to enable gifting items to and from other Stardew Valley worlds?

settings.name: gift_tax
settings.description: Joja Prime will deliver gifts within one business day, for a price! Sending a gift will cost a percentage of the item's monetary value as a tax on the sender.

locations.name: Junimo Kart: The Gem Sea Giant
